{"TopicId":171965,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Battery Charging in 1.4","CreatedByName":"Vkihyone","CreatedById":148778,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-10T20:51:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Vkihyone","CreatedById":148778,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-10T20:51:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I\u0027m running two separate orbital labs, one around the mun and one around kerbin and every time I go back to check on them after moving one of my deep space probes forward 30-40 days (don\u0027t want to miss out on the accumulated science gains) I find that instead of their batteries being fully charged or nearly so they are almost always nearly empty.\u00A0 Now I know I have enough charging capacity to keep them fully powered even while running research so I\u0027m wondering if this is a bug or something else.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-10T20:54:32Z\u0022 title=\u002203/10/2018 08:54  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 10, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Vkihyone\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EFurther testing\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"firda","CreatedById":182404,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-10T21:07:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you leaving when charging or discharging?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-10T21:08:45Z\u0022 title=\u002203/10/2018 09:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 10, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by firda\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Etypo\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vkihyone","CreatedById":148778,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-10T21:11:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI leave while they are charging\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-11T10:35:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223316311\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171965\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520716316\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148778\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vkihyone\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Vkihyone said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI leave while they are charging\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not a bug per se (or it\u0027s so old it\u0027s now classifed as a feature) - batteries don\u0027t charge/discharge while the ship is unloaded. There is a mod for that, but I don\u0027t know if it still works:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9775458045\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/88304-background-processing-0440-ksp-113/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:214px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Temeter","CreatedById":58056,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-11T14:16:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBasically, the batteries shouldn\u0027t be empty, but rather in the same state you left them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jestersage","CreatedById":165777,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-11T17:47:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223316804\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171965\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520764544\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002280345\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022severedsolo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, severedsolo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not a bug per se (or it\u0027s so old it\u0027s now classifed as a feature) - batteries don\u0027t charge/discharge while the ship is unloaded. There is a mod for that, but I don\u0027t know if it still works\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo we need this for lab processing, or is it all good?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vkihyone","CreatedById":148778,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-11T19:31:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh that makes sense (I suppose) thanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}